documentation.text:
@title AgentRegistry
 @notice On-chain registry of agents (wallets) with metadata and reputation.
@notice Set the JobMarket contract (call once after deployment).
@notice Register as an agent. Caller must not already be registered.

@title Escrow
 @notice Holds MON for jobs until release (on completion) or refund (on cancel/dispute).
@notice Lock MON for a job. Called by JobMarket when client posts job (with msg.value forwarded).
@notice Set the agent for a job. Called by JobMarket when agent accepts.
@notice Release payment to agent. Called by JobMarket on job completion.
@notice Refund client. Called by JobMarket on cancel or dispute.

@title JobMarket
 @notice Post jobs, accept, complete, and submit feedback. Integrates AgentRegistry and Escrow.
@notice Post a new job. Caller must be registered and send payment as msg.value.
@notice Accept a job. Caller must be registered agent.
@notice Mark job complete. Only client can call. Releases payment to agent and updates reputation (rating 0 until feedback).
@notice Submit rating 1-100 for the agent. Only client, only once per job, only after completed.
@notice Cancel a posted job (only client, only if still Posted). Refunds client.
@notice Dispute a job (Accepted -> Disputed). Refunds client. Optional: extend later for arbitration.

@title X402Payment
 @notice Records X402 micropayment verification and job linkage for facilitator.
